                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>New Orleans</placeName>. <date>Octr. 23<hi rend=\"sup\"\n                        >rd</hi>. 5611/1850</date>.</p>\n            <p>My dear <addressee>Leeser</addressee>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">I am becoming a frequent correspondt.<lb/> and may possibly weary\n                you with my scribble. However<lb/> the present communication is for your services in\n                aid of<lb/> our proposed Sunday School which will come into operation<lb/> on\n                    <date>Sunday next the 27<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi></date> Inst.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">The Ladies have commissioned me to<lb/> request you will forward by\n                first opportunity the following<lb/> Books.</p>\n            <list type=\"simple\">\n                <head/>\n                <item>3 dz <persName>Miss Peixotto's</persName> Scripture Questions</item>\n                <item>2 dz <persName>Isaac Leeser's</persName> Catechisms</item>\n                <item>3 dz <persName>Nathan's</persName> Derech Emunah<add>?</add></item>\n                <item>4 dz <persName>Pike's</persName> Catechisms</item>\n                <item>1 dz <persName>Solomon's</persName> Mosaic System</item>\n                <item>2 dz <hi rend=\"underline\">Old Testament</hi> Bibles, no headings.</item>\n                <item>A few sets of the American Jewish Library, particularly<lb/> the Epitome of\n                    the Bible, by <persName>Cunery</persName>.</item>\n                <item>1 dz <sic>Matineé's de</sic> Samedi, translated by\n                        <persName>Abrahams</persName><lb/> of\n                    <placeName>Liverpool</placeName></item>\n            </list>\n            <p>together with a small selection of any works used generally by<lb/> the\n                    <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> Sunday School, and a couple of copies\n                of<lb/> their Bye Laws, as also of the Sewing Society, and the full do.<lb/> Please\n                forward the Bill at same times. It would perhaps<lb/> be as well to send the whole\n                by steamer from <placeName>New York</placeName>.<lb/> You may also pack up ½ dz Eu\n                    <persName>Miss Aguilar's</persName> Women of<lb/>\n                <placeName>Israel</placeName>, Jewish Faith, and her other works which you\n                edited,<lb/> these 3 latter on my acct.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Now for a few particulars for the Occident.<lb/> On <date>Sunday the\n                        6<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi></date> Inst. the ladies <sic>worshipping</sic> at\n                the Synagogue<lb/> Dispersed of Judah, held their first meeting at my house,\n                    <persName>Mrs.<lb/> B. Florance</persName> in the chair. Sundry Resolutions were\n                passed<lb/> to be confirmed at the next meeting on <date>Sunday the 13<hi rend=\"sup\"\n                        >th</hi></date>. On<lb/> this occasion 22 ladies offered themselves as\n                teachers, and elected<lb/>\n                <persName>Mrs. B. Florance</persName>\n                <sic>Superintendant</sic>, <persName>Mrs. M. N. Nathan</persName> Treasurer,<lb/>\n                Secy. <persName>Mrs Nathan</persName> declining to accept any office, Mrs.<lb/>\n                <add>?</add>cted in her stead. A Resolution passed requesting</p>\n            <p rend=\"The corner of the page is folded up in the scan, obscuring some words.\"/>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3pn8z18p/canvas/p1"
                }
