                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3pn8z18p/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>the ladies, officers and teachers to collect subscriptions. <date>Sunday<lb/> the\n                        20<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi></date> the ladies had their 3<hi rend=\"sup\">rd</hi>\n                meeting at my house, when<lb/> the sum of $334.20 was handed in as collections. The\n                School<lb/> will be opened the <date>27<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi></date>. I have drawn\n                up a code of Bye<lb/> Laws, and officiated as Secretary; but you must not\n                mention<lb/> it, as I wish the petticoats to have all the credit. You can<lb/>\n                merely say, I gave them my advice and assistance in organizing<lb/> the School. I\n                have every reason to believe the school will<lb/> be very successful. The youth of\n                both sexes belonging to the<lb/> two congregations in the city, and that of\n                    <placeName>Lafayette</placeName> are<lb/> united to attend as pupils; but the\n                government of the School<lb/> will be managed by the ladies <sic>worshipping</sic>\n                at the Portuguese<lb/> Synagogue, who are now or may hereafter become teachers.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I wish to be informed respecting a female who<lb/> came here some\n                weeks ago, a widow, calling herself <persName>Mrs. Rice</persName><lb/> who says she\n                has long resided in your city, where her husband<lb/> kept a large\n                    <sic>Jeweller's</sic> shop. Her uncle, according to her acct<lb/> resides there\n                now, his name is <persName>Brühl</persName>. Her story is to this effect.<lb/> A\n                sister named <persName>Fernbein</persName> living at\n                    <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName> wrote for her<lb/> and on arriving at that\n                city, she found her sister had removed<lb/> to <placeName>N. O.</placeName> No such\n                persons, after due inquiry, could be found<lb/> here; and she applied for assistance\n                to go back to <placeName>Pa</placeName><lb/> to her uncle. From many circumstances,\n                people here think<lb/> she is somewhat of an impostor. I am half inclined to\n                that<lb/> opinion myself. However some money was made up for her<lb/> to enable her\n                to return via <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName>. She <sic>quitted</sic>\n                yesterday.<lb/> She told us her child was poisoned some years ago by her<lb/>\n                servant girl. The impression she made has been any thing but<lb/> favourable even\n                upon those who espoused her cause.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">All your friends whose name is <persName>Legion</persName> send<lb/>\n                their regards, and hoping your health is<lb/> improving, and with best wishes in which<lb/>\n                <persName>Mrs. N.</persName> joins I am Truly yours</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(9)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">M N Nathan</persName>\n            </p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3pn8z18p/canvas/p2"
